Although we are working on many open roles at the moment my approach to you is not with a particular requirement in mind. It is more on the basis that I saw you were open to new opportunities and I wanted to organize an introductory call with myself to discuss your current situation and potential motivations to move at this point in time  Given we work with a number of companies in this industry we have close relationships with decision makers and top-level HR, which for positions at your level are the people that can make a decision on your profile.  We do a lot of work in this sector and appreciate that despite the size of the industry it is a small world and people know each other! With this in mind we work with the upmost discretion and confidentiality  If you are open to looking outside of your current company and keen to understand what the market and what Mackinnon Bruce could offer you then, please let me know and we can look to discuss further.  I have a number of available time slots on Monday next week, so please let me know a 30-minute window that works best for you. David McDonald Business Development Intern | Mackinnon Bruce International

SUBJECT: Quantum Computer Curiosity, and admiration
CONTENT: Dear Dr. Gershon  I've seen some of your videos on YouTube passionately talking about Quantum computing and you've made me very curious for your field.  This might seem unrelated, but I'm about to join a Marie Curie PhD in DNA nanotechnology and while looking for possible applications for the technique I'm about to get into (DNA Origami) I have seen its potential for nanopatterning. I'm excited about the possibilities of using DNA as a scaffolding material at the nanoscale and I figured that it could be used to fabricate some complex architectures.  If it was possible, would you kindly point me towards the techniques or some research groups that tackle the issue of fabricating the quantum computers? Just the practical, hand on part to see if I can figure out a way to put Origami to work towards that goal.  And if i come across a cool idea, would you be open to have a collaboration?  Thanks in advance for reading  Best regards, Aitor

CONVERSATION TITLE: Accelerate your career with an Executive miniMBA from LSBF
CONTENT:
Dear Aitor,

 

Are you looking to boost your career and gain a new set of skills to become a leader in your field? I believe I have the right course for you to help you achieve your career goals in 2021, despite the global pandemic challenges you might be facing. 

 

My name is Kreshnik and I am the Head of Student Recruitment at London School of Business and Finance. I came across your profile and thought you would be the ideal candidate for the Executive miniMBA programme we are running live-online at London School of Business and Finance. 

 

Your profile and experience aligns well with the course content and gaining this certificate will certainly help broaden your skills and excel in your role. 

 

During this course you will be able to learn how to make strategic business decisions, gain an understanding of some of the fundamentals of finance for senior management, learn how to identify and recognise the need for change in your organisation, and much more. 

 

Additionally, the Executive miniMBA offers:


  • Live interactive classes with delegates from different industries.
  • Flexible schedule with evening sessions.
  • Flexible payment options.
  • An LSBF certificate of completion and an official CPD (Continuing Professional Development) certificate that may count towards your CPD goals.
  • First-hand industry knowledge through a number of case studies.

 

To learn more about the Executive miniMBA, please click on "Learn More" and submit your details.

 

I look forward to welcoming you on board with London School of Business and Finance! 

 

Regards,

 

Kreshnik Boraj,

Head of Student Recruitment LSBF
